The paper deals with graph algorithms and data structures, specifically the construction of spanners and hopsets. This falls under the category of "Data Structures and Algorithms" (cs.DS) and "Computational Geometry" (cs.CG). The paper also involves analysis of the stretch factor and size of the constructed structures, which could fall under "Numerical Analysis" (cs.NA) and "Discrete Mathematics" (cs.DM). Finally, the paper mentions the use of these structures in practical applications such as network routing, which could fall under "Social and Information Networks" (cs.SI).
